@page "/copilot-summary"

<PageTitle>Copilot Summary - EventEase</PageTitle>

<div class="page-intro">
    <div>
        <span class="page-kicker">Submission Note</span>
        <h1 class="page-title">How Copilot Assisted the Development Process</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">This short reflection explains how Microsoft Copilot contributed at each stage of the EventEase project, from first component generation to the final cleanup pass.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="page-chip">Required reflection</div>
</div>

<div class="summary-list">
    <section>
        <h3>Step 1: Foundational Component Generation</h3>
        <p>Copilot helped generate the first version of the Event Card component with fields for title, location, date, description, and seat count. It also suggested the two-way binding pattern used to edit event data directly from the UI.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Step 2: Routing Implementation</h3>
        <p>Copilot provided guidance for structuring the application into dedicated pages and wiring up route-based navigation. That made it easier to organize the dashboard, events, registration, attendance, session state, and summary pages.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Step 3: Debugging and Optimization</h3>
        <p>Copilot was used to troubleshoot routing issues, service registration problems, and form behavior. It also helped refine validation and remove structural issues that hurt usability.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Step 4: Advanced Features</h3>
        <p>Copilot suggested patterns for the registration workflow, data-annotation validation, session state management, and a simple attendance tracker with check-in updates.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Step 5: Final Review and Cleanup</h3>
        <p>Copilot assisted with polishing the project structure, improving naming consistency, refining the layout, and adding the new event creation flow before packaging the app for GitHub submission.</p>
    </section>
</div>
